The paper discusses the need for intelligent information management in database systems, which suggests a focus on database management (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of intelligent computing paradigms and flexible querying also suggests a potential overlap with information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the mention of efficient interactions between database and users may indicate a consideration of software engineering (cs.SE) principles.
